Data Visualization

ggplot(penguins, aes(x = bill_length)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1.5, color = "black", fill = "skyblue2") +
  facet_wrap(~ species, scales = "free") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Bill Length by Species", x = "Bill Length", y = "Frequency") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.title = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10)
  )

ggplot(penguins, aes(x = bill_length, y = bill_depth)) +
  geom_point(color = "skyblue2", size = 2.5) +
  facet_wrap(~ species, scales = "free") +
  labs(title = "Relationship between Bill Length and Depth by Species", x = "Bill Length", y = "Bill Depth") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.title = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10)
  )

ggplot(penguins, aes(x = species, y = bill_length)) +
  geom_boxplot(color = "skyblue3", fill = "skyblue2") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of bill length by species", x = "Species", y = "Bill Length") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.title = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10)
  )

ggplot(penguins, aes(x = bill_length, y = bill_depth, color = sex)) +
  geom_point(size = 2.5) +
  labs(title = "Correlation between Bill Length, Depth, and Sex", x = "Bill Length", y = "Bill Depth") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),

Modelling

# For Separate Model
data_separate <- list(
  N = nrow(penguins),
  K = length(unique(penguins$species)),
  bill_length = penguins$bill_length,
  species = as.integer(factor(penguins$species)),
  bill_depth = penguins$bill_depth,
  penguin_sex = penguins$sex
)

# For Hierarchical Model
data_hierarchical <- list(
  N = nrow(penguins),
  K = length(unique(penguins$species)),
  bill_length = penguins$bill_length,
  species = as.integer(factor(penguins$species)),
  bill_depth = penguins$bill_depth,
  penguin_sex = penguins$sex
)
